  "summary": "This tomatoey kidney bean curry, with fragrant gingery spices, is a simple yet satisfying dish that makes the most of store cupboard ingredients. This recipe combines tender kidney beans with a rich tomato sauce, flavoured with aromatic spices like cumin, coriander, and ginger. The result is a hearty, comforting meal that’s both delicious and budget-friendly. Perfect for a quick weeknight dinner, this curry is packed with flavor and nutrition, thanks to the protein-rich beans and nutrient-dense tomatoes. Whether you serve it over fluffy rice or with warm naan bread, it’s a versatile dish that doesn’t skimp on taste despite its simplicity. The use of readily available ingredients means you can whip up this meal with minimal fuss, making it a go-to recipe for those days when you want something easy yet deeply satisfying",
